    "content": "B — the Translator's Afterword.\n\nThis finding is philosophically significant and belongs in the cross-traditional connections section. However, it cannot go in the Preface for two reasons: (1) it reveals the conclusion of the author's entire philosophical trajectory — the shift from \"how do I become authentic?\" to \"how do I notice that I already am?\" is the experiential destination the collection is designed to bring the reader to, and stating it in advance would be a spoiler of the deepest kind; (2) it requires the reader to have already encountered the Poetic, the dreamscape concept, and the Appendix passage to have any experiential grounding. In the Afterword, the reader has completed the journey and can recognize this insight as articulating something they have already felt — which is precisely the epistemological structure (eta as confirmation of what was experientially produced) the framework describes."
